HEADWORD: Greenstone
<hw>Green"stone`</hw> <pr>(gr⟦emac⟧n"st⟦omac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[So called from a tinge of green in the color.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A name formerly applied rather loosely to
certain dark-colored igneous rocks, including diorite, diabase,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greensward</ent>⟦br⟧
